		<outline text="What is a /now page?" created="Fri, 10 Apr 2020 19:22:49 GMT" collapse="true">
			<outline text="In 2015 &lt;a href=&quot;https://sivers.org/nowff&quot;&gt;Derek Sivers proposed&lt;/a&gt; that people add a &quot;/now&quot; page to their personal web sites that simply answers, what are you doing now? The idea caught on and there is even a now pages index on &lt;a href=&quot;https://nownownow.com/&quot;&gt;nownownow.com&lt;/a&gt;. " created="Fri, 10 Apr 2020 19:22:53 GMT"/>
			<outline text="The challenge, it seems to me, is in the maintenance of said /now page. When I learned that Dave had released a new &lt;a href=&quot;http://my.this.how/davewiner/howtosInLittleOutliner.opml&quot;&gt;dynamic publishing feature&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=&quot;http://littleoutliner.com&quot;&gt;Little Outliner&lt;/a&gt; it seemed it might be a good way to create my own /now page, even if it is hosted on another domain." created="Fri, 10 Apr 2020 19:25:52 GMT"/>
